{
  "stem": "1753.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I recall, in fact, that a certain number of Jewish families that had their children in public school, and that could afford it, took their sons or daughters out of-- from the public schools and sent them to a Jewish school on a daily basis.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They took the train from-- from Breisach to Freiburg, which is in the Black Forest-- a sizable city.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They went there every day, in the morning, and came back in the evening.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But my mother-- we couldn't afford it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the Jewish community-- at that particular time, they didn't want to spend the money.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So people-- unless the parents were able to fund that Jewish education, that other little city, for others it wasn't possible.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in any case, so I lived in that little town.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then in 1936, I was bar mitzvahed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a very nice but small affair.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my mother, and my brother, and my sister came.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was-- that event, two, three days, and then they went back and I stayed there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And finally, in 1938, in April, I graduated from the public school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they-- and I was sent to a city by the name of Karlsruhe, which was the-- the capital of the province Baden.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there, there was a Jewish electrical engineer, who was quite prominent in the city.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he still had his business intact.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I had a job to learn the elect-- I got a job with him as a trainee, as an apprentice, to learn electrical engineering.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So that was in April of 1938.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there again, he-- his clientele by that time had shrunk basically to the Jewish businesses that needed that type of work.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
